# Notification service credentials.
#
# Copy to discord.env (same directory) and fill in the real value. discord.env
# is gitignored — never commit it. run.sh sources this file into the process
# environment before launching the service.
#
# ─── Discord webhook URL ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# A Discord channel webhook URL. Format:
#   https://discord.com/api/webhooks/<id>/<token>
# The token suffix carries the auth — anyone with this URL can post to the
# channel. Treat it as a secret-equivalent bearer credential: if ever
# committed in plaintext, rotate it in Discord — a git history rewrite
# does not un-expose it. (Same rule as the TTN / CIMIS keys.)
DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/000000000000000000/xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Optional: the bot display name shown on each message. Defaults to
# "fleet_design" if unset.
# NOTIFY_USERNAME=fleet_design
